<HEADLINE> Good Start at Asiad for Hong Kong, China Team: Tung </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee
Hwa of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) said
that the Hong Kong, China team had made a good start Monday with
cyclist Brian Cook winning a bronze medal in the men's mountain bi
ke downhill event at the 13th Asian Games in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
In a congratulatory message to Timothy Fok, president of the
Amateur Sports Association and Olympic Committee of Hong Kong,
China, Tung said: "This is a very good start for the Hong Kong
SAR team. I am sure that under your outstanding leadership, our
athletes will continue to bring honor to Hong Kong."
</P>
<P>
"I take this opportunity to wish all the SAR athletes every
success in the Games," he said.
</P>
<P>
Fok is now in Bangkok, attending a meeting of the Olympic
Council of Asia, the regional governing body for Olympic sports.
</P>
