<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Stock Shares Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The value of shares trade on
the Zimbabwe Stock Exchange (ZSE) fell sharply by 56.1 percent in
the third quarter of this year due to depressed investor
confidence, the Zimbabwe Financial Holdings has said.
</P>
<P>
The bank said in its latest economic bulletin released Monday
in Harare that "investor sentiment on the Zimbabwe stock market
remained depressed mainly due to high inflation and interest
rates as well as an unstable currency."
</P>
<P>
It said as a result local investors shifted their focus from
the equity market to the money market where short-term returns
were comparatively higher and more certain.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors' sentiment was affected by the financial and
economic problems facing other emerging stock markets,
particularly the economic turmoil in Russia and Southeast Asia.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
