<HEADLINE> France Concerned about Fighting in Comoran Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 7 (Xinhua) -- France expressed concern on
Monday over the fighting which broke out last Saturday in the
Comoran island of Anjouan in the Indian Ocean.
</P>
<P>
France appealed to the conflicting sides of Anjouan to start
dialogue and show restraint, said the foreign ministry here.
</P>
<P>
The militias loyal to the central government and those calling
for independence fought on the island on Saturday, killing at
least 10 people.
</P>
<P>
France recalled that the heads of state of African countries
and France had expressed their support to the Comoran interim
president Tedjidine ben Said Massonde during the 20th
African-French summit in Paris late last month.
</P>
<P>
The heads of state also supported the Organization of African
Unity in its mediation of the conflicting sides in the archipelago
by holding an "inter-Comoran conference" soon.  
</P>
</TEXT>
