<HEADLINE> Clinton Removes Iran from List of Drug Problem </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton,
showing another gesture to Iran for improvement of relations
between the two countries, Monday removed Iran from the U.S.
blacklist of drug problem countries.
</P>
<P>
He said in a letter to members of Congress that he did so
because Iran had carried out a successful program to eradicate
opium poppy plants.
</P>
<P>
He said while Iran still is a transit point for opiates
heading for Europe, there is no evidence to suggest that
significant quantities arrive in the United States.  
</P>
</TEXT>
