<HEADLINE> Palestinians Demonstrations Spread in West Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Dozens of Palestinians were
injured in West Bank cities on Monday when Israeli soldiers
clamped down their demonstrations for the release of Palestinian
prisoners.
</P>
<P>
At least 20 Palestinians were lightly hurt as they clashed
with Israeli soldiers who guarded a Jewish holy site near
Bethlehem. The demonstrators threw stones at the soldiers, who
responded with rubber-coated bullets and tear gas.
</P>
<P>
On the ourskirts of Ramallah, eight Palestinians were wounded
during their clashes with Israeli troops.
</P>
<P>
In Hebron, Palestinians clashed with Israeli soldiers near the
Israeli-controlled Jewish neighborhood. And three Palestinians
were injured.
</P>
<P>
And a Palestinian was seriously wounded when an Israeli
civilian fired at the demonstrators with a gun after his car
was stoned by them near east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Several Israeli soldiers were wounded in the clashes with the
Palestinians all over the West Bank, according to the Israeli
radio.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Palestinian demonstrators also confronted with
the Palestinian police in some locations as the latter tried
to stop them from moving out the Palestinian-controlled areas.
</P>
<P>
In Nabulus, about three thousands protesters marched toward
the Jewish patriarch Joseph's tomb on the outskirts of the
city. And they were confronted with dozens of the Palestinian
policemen, who tried to halt the march with clubs. Three of them
were injured.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Palestinian Prisoners Association on
Monday called for a new Palestinian intifada (uprising) until all
three Palestinian prisoners in Israeli jails were freed.
</P>
<P>
Israeli security forces said Monday the Palestinians would
continue and possibly intensify their demonstrations as the
U.S. President Bill Clinton was expected to arrive in the region
on Saturday night. 
</P>
</TEXT>
