<HEADLINE> Three Highways Now Open In South China Autonomous Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The highways between Liuzhou
and Wangling, between Nanning and Nanjian, and between
Jinchengjiang and Yizhou opened to traffic simultaneously today in
south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The 65 km-long six-lane expressway from Nanning to Nanjian is
designed for a speed of 120 km per hour. and is the best part of
the Nanning-Beihai expressway as far as quality is concerned.
</P>
<P>
The 138-km-long Liuzhou-Wangling expressway connects the
Guilin-Liuzhou expressway in the north and the Binyang-Nanning
expressway, which is still being built, in the south, and is a
trunk highway running through Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
The four-lane Jinchengjiang-Yizhou highway is 68 km long, and
is designed for speeds of 100 km per hour.
</P>
<P>
The three highways cost 1.7 billion yuan (205 million
U.S. dollars), 2.15 billion yuan (260 million US dollars) and 501
million yuan (60.5 million US dollars), respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
