<HEADLINE> Finland Cancels Nicaragua's 18-Million-Dollar Debt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Finnish government
announced Wednesday that it will cancel Nicaragua's 90-million
Finnish markka (18 million U.S. dollars) debt due to the heavy
damage inflicted by Hurricane Mitch on the central American
country.
</P>
<P>
Finland hoped the remission may help Nicaragua launch its
recovery plan, said a Finnish senior official.
</P>
<P>
The two long-term loans to Nicaragua in 1988 and 1991 were used
to buy fertilizers, papermaking facilities and to provide energy
for the capital, Managua.
</P>
<P>
From 1988 to 1991, Finland loaned nearly 200 million markkas to
Nicaragua, of which 103 million markkas were already cancelled in
1993.
</P>
<P>
In the beginning of November, the Finnish government provided
three million markkas in emergency aid to Nicaragua and other
central American countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
