<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Steel Manufacturers Doing Away With Open Hearth Furnaces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Wuhan Iron and Steel Group
started using its revolving furnace No.1, an improved open hearth
furnace, today, meaning that all of its open hearth furnaces have
been replaced by the more advanced revolving furnaces.
</P>
<P>
The replacement project cost 650 million yuan and took eight
months to complete. A senior official at the company says that the
conversion simplified and shortened the production process,
reduced energy consumption, and cut the cost per ton by 200 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The cost is expected to be recovered in two years' time.
</P>
<P>
The official says that putting in a new revolving furnace
factory of the same size would cost 2 billion yuan, so the
conversion process was the most cost-effective.
</P>
<P>
According to a Metallurgical Industry Administration plan from
earlier this year, China will stop the use of all open hearth
furnaces by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
The replacement of open hearth furnaces at Wuhan and the Anshan
Iron and Steel Group is expected to bring the nation's annual
open-hearth steel production down to 3 million tons from 5 million
tons next year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
