<HEADLINE> China's First Dishwasher Manufacture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Little Swan Merloni
Dishwasher Co., Ltd., a joint venture of Wuxi Little Swan Corp., a
national washing machine manufacturer, and Italy's Merloni Corp.,
a large electric appliance producer, became China's first
dishwasher manufacturer today.
</P>
<P>
The new company cost 29.8 million U.S. dollars, with 75 percent
of that coming from Little Swan, and the rest from Merloni.
</P>
<P>
According to Jiang Dahua, general manager of the joint venture,
his company will be the largest dishwasher producer in Asia, with
annual production capacity expected to be 800,000 units.
</P>
<P>
Dishwashers can be found in 50-60 percent of the households in
developed countries and sales in some Asian countries are growing
20 percent annually.
</P>
<P>
The household dishwasher is thought by many to be the second
major household appliance to get rid of a significant amount of
traditional housework, after the washing machine.
</P>
<P>
Jiang says the company's products will sell for half the cost
of imports in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
