<HEADLINE> German Unemployment Rate Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- German unemployment rose by 54,300
to 3,946,000 in November, the Federal Labor Office said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Nuremberg-based office said the unemployment rate went up
by 0.1 percent from October to 10.2 percent in November.
</P>
<P>
The office noted that November's unemployment was 375,600 less
than the corresponding period last year, and the increase was
within the usual numbers seen when winter weather started to
reduce outdoor work.
</P>
<P>
In western Germany, 8.8 percent of the workforce, or 2,744,800
people, were unemployed in November. In eastern Germany, the
jobless rate stood at 15.9 percent, with 1,201,200 people out of
work.
</P>
<P>
Labor Office president Bernhard Jagoda said there were signs
of future improvement in the job market despite the slight drop in
employment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Federal Statistics Office in Wiesbaden has
reported that job prospects are looking up as September employment
stood at 34.5 million, representing a rise of 175,000 over the
same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
