<HEADLINE> World Demand for Oil Drops in 4th Quarter of 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The world demand for oil,
particularly in the industrialized countries, has dropped by 650,000
barrels per day to 75.7 million barrels a day in the fourth
quarter of 1998, said the International Energy Agency (IEA) on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
World oil stocks are now at a very high level and the price of
crude fell in November to its lowest in 12 years, said the IEA in
its monthly report.
</P>
<P>
The production of oil around the world has increased by 800,000
barrels a day in November to 75 million barrels a day,
according to the IEA.
</P>
<P>
Non-OPEC countries contributed up to 70 percent of that
increase, while OPEC countries failed in their promise to reduce
production last month, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
