<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank's ATM Network Open To International Cardholders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China today signed
an agreement with American Express to allow its cardholders access
to the bank's ATM network in China.
</P>
<P>
This will give American Express cardholders immediate access to
526 BOC ATMs. Another 2,100 ATMs will be available in 1999. These
are in addition to the 205,000 ATMs in 56 countries open to
American Express cardholders.
</P>
<P>
BOC is the only Chinese bank that has opened its ATM network to
other cardholders. Its ATM network is available to Visa and
Mastercard International. Its new computerized creditcard network
opened early this year and can be accessed through more than 600
ATM machines in Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin, Xiamen and some cities
in Guangdong and Jiangsu provinces.
</P>
<P>
American Express has more than 1,700 branches around the world,
and 40 million card users. Its card is accepted at more than
20,000 hotels, restaurants, shops and airlines in China. 
</P>
