<HEADLINE> HK Imports New Shock Wave Machine From Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong has imported from
Germany Extracorporeal Shock Wave Therapy (ESWT) machine, the
first of its kind in the region, which is capable of serving more
patients suffering from tendopathies and pseudarthrosis.
</P>
<P>
The machine has been installed in the 13-year-old Shock Wave
Therapy Center of the St. Paul's Hospital located on Hong Kong
Island.
</P>
<P>
"The ESWT is effective in most cases that have been resistant
to usual conservative methods such as medication, physiotherapy
and steroid injection," said Dr. Christine Bachmann, chief of the
Shock Wave Therapy Center of Germany, at a press conference here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The procedure is simple, safe, non-invasive and hospitalization
is unnecessary. Both X-ray and ultrasound can be used for
localization purposes. The effectiveness and success of such
treatment is 70 to 80 percent, Bachmann said. 
</P>
