<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poverty Is Human Rights Violation, Says UN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- "Poverty is human rights
violation, and freedom from poverty is an integral and
inalienable human right," Samuel Nyambi, United Nations Resident
Coordinator and United Nations Development Program (UNDP)
Resident Representative, said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here to mark the 50th
anniversary of the Universal Declaration of Human Rights, Nyambi
said: "As Africa today is experiencing a wave of democratization,
most African country leaders are convinced that peace,
development and democracy are mutually reinforcing."
</P>
<P>
He noted that UNDP's overriding and central priority is
poverty eradication within a Sustainable Human Development
Framework, adding that without the basic democratic, social and
cultural rights it would be difficult to attain the development
objectives and most particularly food security which is the most
challenging aspect of African continent.
</P>
<P>
"UNDP places human rights, good governance and sustainable
human development as interdependent and mutually reinforcing
conditions for eradicating poverty," he said.
</P>
<P>
Judith Lewis, World Food Program (WFP) Resident
Representative, said at the press conference that there are an
estimated 800 million people around the world who do not have
adequate access to food.
</P>
<P>
She said one of the principal objectives of WFP is to save the
lives of people whose ability to gain access to food has been
curtailed.
</P>
<P>
"Eradicating hunger, which afflicts one out of every seven
people on earth, cannot be achieved without creating conditions
that help people become more self-reliant," she stressed.
</P>
<P>
Hamaoly Lamine Conde, regional office director of the United
Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization
(UNESCO), said the UNESCO will put the emphasis on children in
general and street children in particular during the program of
activities to mark the 50th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
He said the objectives of the program are, first to promote
the education for human rights, peace and democracy; second to
draw attention of the public on the condition and needs of the
street children; and third to promote the work of all those who
work with the children in need.
</P>
<P>
The press conference is part of the programs launched by the
UN agencies here to mark the 50th anniversary of the Universal
Declaration of Human Rights which was adopted by the UN General
Assembly in 1948. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
