<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Rises 23.84 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday closed at 2,945.64
points as against Monday's close of 2,921.80, netting a rise of
23.84 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index looked up by 9.18 points to 1,307.89 from
previous close of 1,298.71.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted fractionally
up at 302.98 and 118.44 points compared with previous close of
301.23 and 117.81 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities forged moderately ahead with pharmaceutical and
software scrips in the lead on the stock market Tuesday on
sustained support from foreign institutional investors and
financial institutions. 
</P>
