<HEADLINE> Iran, Iraq Swap Remains of Killed Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Iraq on Tuesday
swapped the remains of 121 Iranian and 213 Iraqi soldiers killed
in the 1980-1988 war, Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The exchange took place at the border point of Shalamcheh,
Iran's southwestern province of Khuzestan, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It added that Shalamcheh was the area in which many Iranian
soldiers were killed in eight battles fought against Iraqi forces.
</P>
<P>
This was the fourth exchange of remains of killed soldiers
between the two sides since they started joint search operations
in May.
</P>
<P>
During the previous three swaps, the two former foes
repatriated the remains of 264 Iranians and 234 Iraqis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
