<HEADLINE> Share Prices Extend Gains on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices extended gains
on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday on lingering expectations of
another round of interest rate cuts.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) moved up 16.79 points
to close at 1,393.61 points with rate-sensitive stocks, such as
banks and properties, hogging the limelight.
</P>
<P>
Total turnover rebounded to 237.49 million units worth 561.47
million Singapore dollars (338.44 million U.S. dollars). Gainers
outnumbered losers by 177 to 74 with 169 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
KepBank topped the actives chart of the day with a turnover of
18.02 million units traded. DBS Land was the second most heavily
traded share with a volume of 12.61 million units done. ST Engg
was next with 9.85 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SPH 100 was the biggest gainer of the day with an 80-cent jump
to 17.80 Singapore dollars. UOB F surged 45 cents to end at 10.00
Singapore dollars. UOB went up 40 cents to finish at 6.20
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, F &AMP; N led the descent of the day with a loss
of 35 cents to 5.15 Singapore dollars. Venture shed 30 cents to
close at 5.70 Singapore dollars. Jar Str sank 17 cents to end at
1.51 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Share prices soared at midday trading on mounting expectation
of interest rate cuts, pushing through the 1,400-point level.
</P>
<P>
Analysts believed that with interbank rates stabilizing around
2 percent, major local banks are expected to cut their prime
lending rates further.
</P>
<P>
But the market ran out of steam in the afternoon trading and
the STI ended way off its intra-day high of 1,416.33. 
</P>
</TEXT>
