<HEADLINE> Fujian Province Cooperating With Taiwan In Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province
plans to promote tourism cooperation with Taiwan, Hong Kong, and
Macao in the coming year, according to Ming Min, director of the
Provincial Travel Bureau.
</P>
<P>
This includes accelerating the development of postal, trade,
air, and shipping services to Taiwan and cooperation with Hong
Kong and Macao in transport.
</P>
<P>
Ming said that Fujian will first promote two-way tourism
between its coastal city of Xiamen and Taiwan's Jinmen Island,
just off the coast of Xiamen, and trying to turn Xiamen into a
port city for Taiwan compatriots to travel and do business in the
mainland.
</P>
<P>
