<DOCNO> XIE19981208.0146 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on President Jiang's Visit to Japan (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhu continued that the two sides agreed that to ensure sound,
stable and lasting Sino-Japanese relations in the new century is
in the fundamental interests of the people of the two countries,
and that they would both make positive contributions to peace and
development in the Asia-Pacific region and the world at large.
</P>
<P>
To this end, the two sides, in the spirit of learning lessons
from history and to face the future positively, announced the
establishment of a friendly and cooperative partnership devoted to
peace and development, which highlighted the direction of progress
in bilateral relations and marked a new stage in the development
of bilateral ties, noted Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Both sides have also discussed long-term prospects and worked
out an overall plan for the future growth of bilateral ties,
agreeing to strengthen non-governmental friendly exchanges
including the youth program, conduct forward-looking cooperation
in high- and new-tech industries and environmental protection, and
make efforts to help overcome the financial crisis in east Asia
while promoting regional stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
As to the repeated questions about why the Sino-Japanese joint
declaration was not signed, Zhu stressed that President Jiang had
answered the question at a press conference in Japan, but that he
would reiterate it.
</P>
<P>
Zhu explained that during the discussions between the two sides
on the matter of a joint declaration, they did not consider the
issue of signing at that stage, and there was no such an
arrangement in the schedule agreed between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony after the talks between Jiang and Obuchi
was for the three cooperative documents, not for the declaration,
added Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, he added, there have been similar documents drawn
up between China and many countries that were not signed. However,
this factor will not have any impact on the effect of these
documents, Zhu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
