<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ADB Okays Loans to Three Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Manila, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank (ADB)
Tuesday approved loans to Kiribati, Nepal and Papua New Guinea to
finance these countries' industry or environment projects.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said in its news release that water supply, sewerage,
solid waste disposal and environment conservation in Kiribati
would be improved by ADB's loan of 10.24 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The ADB's loan of 20 million U.S. dollars to Nepal would help
nearly 270,000 poor households in the country's rural area start
their own enterprises in a micro finance project.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ADB approved 6.5 million U.S. dollars to finance
Papua New Guinea in developing local participation in its huge
fisheries industry, currently dominated by foreign interests.
</P>
</TEXT>
