<HEADLINE> Tian Challenges Sautin with Win in Platform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 8 (Xinhua) -- World silver medallist Tian
Liang of China threw down the gauntlet to world champion Dmitry
Sautin of Ukraine here on Tuesday when he led all the way to win
the men's platform title in the Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
Tian, 19, who won the silver in the World Championships in
Perth, Australia in January, garnered 657.660 points to win the
gold.
</P>
<P>
His teammate Huang Qiang, 16, finished second in 574.020 with
the bronze went to Suchart Pichi of Thailand, who collected
559.890 points.
</P>
<P>
Tian, who lost to Sautin in the World Championships and the
Goodwill Games and finished runner-up, said: "My nemesis in the
2000 Sydney Olympics will still be Sautin."
</P>
<P>
Though never beating Sautin in major competitions, Tian is very
confident of his chance agaist the tough opponent.
</P>
<P>
"I'm injury-free now and if I work hard the next two years, I
will beat him in the Olympics."
</P>
<P>
Tian said he failed to bring out his best in the competition.
"The tally points I got today is almost 20 shy of my best," he
said, "As there is no real rivals here, so if I can dive
consistently, I will win the gold."
</P>
<P>
Tian's coach Zhang Ting said the next two years are very
important for his protege if he wants to beat Sautin.
</P>
<P>
"Whether or not can he beat Sautin to win the Olympic gold in
Sydney, it depends on these two years' work," Zhang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
