<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Stamps Issued in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 8 (Xinhua) -- A new set of stamps were issued
by the Macao Posts and Telecommunications Department (CTT) here on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Entitled Glazed Tiles in Macao, the four stamps in the
philatelic issue have face values of one pataca, 1.5 patacas, 2.5
patacas and 5.5 patacas. Eight patacas are equal to one U.S.
dollar.
</P>
<P>
Being a major means of decoration, glazed tiles have been used
to depict profuse religious and cultural creations in both China
and Portugal.
</P>
<P>
The themes chosen for the stamps feature dragon and phoenix
(two kinds of most important mythical animals in traditional
Chinese culture), and the vessel and junk used by Portuguese
sailors centuries ago.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, CTT has issued all the 12 sets of stamps scheduled
for 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
