<HEADLINE> Trade Fair on Township-Run Enterprises Cooperation Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) --A record number of 10,000
entrepreneurs from all over China attended the first ever
Trade Fair staged here, three times more than expected.
</P>
<P>
The four-day Fair, which ended today, focused on East-West
cooperation among Township-run enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It saw 1,752 contracts with a total trade value of 15 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, over 1,000 counties and villages from various
provinces forged new economic ties with interested partners.
</P>
<P>
The central and western parts of China enjoy rich natural
resources and contain two thirds of the country's population.
</P>
<P>
However, the regions have long lagged behind other parts of
the country in terms of economic development because of a shortage
of funds and a poor environment.
</P>
<P>
The Trade Fair, which will now be an annual event, is aimed at
promoting economic cooperation between rural enterprises in the
eastern coastal and the central and western areas of China
</P>
