<DOCNO> XIE19981208.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-08 10:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan President to Visit Iran Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel Arap
Moi is expected to arrive here next week for an official visit,
the daily Iran News reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan ambassador to Tehran al-Haj Mohammed Soba told the
daily in an interview that Moi's visit is aimed at boosting
political, economic and cultural ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Soba hoped Moi's upcoming visit will lead to easing of travel
regulations and visa requirements between Iran and Kenya so as to
facilitate mutual visits by traders and tourists to each other
country.
</P>
<P>
The trade balance between the two countries is in Iran's favor
due to Kenyan purchases of Iranian crude, paraffin wax and textile
materials, he disclosed.
</P>
<P>
He said that Kenya is trying to bring about a more
proportioned trade balance between the two countries by promoting
exports of Kenya's major products including tea, coffee and
tropical fruits such as pineapples and mangoes.
</P>
<P>
Kenya is studying the possibility of using Iran as a transit
route for getting its products to the markets in the Commonwealth
of Independent States, the Kenyan envoy said.
</P>
<P>
He also named tourism as one of the fields for Tehran and
Nairobi cooperation, saying Kenya is willing to transfer its
experience in the tourist industry to Iran. 
</P>
</TEXT>
