<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Teenager Wins Asiad Women's Air Pistol Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan teenager Dina
Aspandiyarova took the women's air pistol gold at the Asian Games
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"I am not satisfied with my result," said Aspandiyarova after
scoring 486.8 points to beat the Asian Games record set by Chinese
Wang Lina in Beijing in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Aspandiyarova said she was hungry for victory before the final.
</P>
<P>
"I was ready to win. I wanted to win. I did everything as I
could to win," said the 17-year-old student from Kazakhstan's
State University of Foreign Languages.
</P>
<P>
Chinese shooters carried home the silver and bronze medals,
with Cai Yeqing notching 486.0 points and Ren Jie registering
484.6.
</P>
<P>
Cai, who won the sports pistol gold at this year's world
championships, said she was a bit nervous during the competition.
</P>
<P>
"Occasionally, I even did not think I was holding the gun
properly. So I had to raise or lower the pistol several times,"
said Cai. 
</P>
