<HEADLINE> . hke120828--Philippines Okays Duty-Free Imports of Farm, Fishery Inputs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines has allowed the
duty-free importation of agriculture and fishery inputs in a bid
to enhance the productivity and modernize the two sectors, the
Philippines News Agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
This came about after Agriculture Secretary William Dar,
Finance Secretary Edgardo Espiritu and Trade and Industry
Secretary Jose Pardo signed an order covering the duty-free
importation of agricultural products.
</P>
<P>
The order covers two batches of farm and fishery inputs,
machinery and equipment that can be imported within the next five
years by qualified farm, fishery firms, farmers and fishers'
cooperatives and organizations.
</P>
<P>
The farm and fishery inputs, machinery and equipment include
pure bred livestock, plant and seed materials, farm tractors,
packaging machinery, drip irrigation system, post-harvest machines
for vegetables and other crops and sugar machinery. 
</P>
</TEXT>
