<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Indonesia's Flores Island </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.5 on
the Richter scale jolted Indonesia's Flores island in East Nusa
Tenggara province at 07:30 local time Tuesday, according to Antara
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was situated at 8.49 degrees south
latitude and 121.43 degrees north latitude, head of the provincial
meteorological and geophysical office Ibnu Purwana said.
</P>
<P>
Its epicenter was traced 33 kilometers beneath the sea level or
about 40 kilometers east of Riung subdistrict, Ngada district,
some 90 kilometers northwest of Maumere district town of Sika.
</P>
<P>
There was no report of casualty and material loss, Antara said.
</P>
</TEXT>
