<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beat Tajikistan 3-1 in Asiad Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 8 (Xinhua) -- China beat Tajikistan 3-1 for
their first victory in the second round of the Asiad soccer
tournament on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, runners-up at the Hiroshima Asian Games, took
an early lead at the 8th minute when Zhao Junzhe beat a off-side
trap to put China 1-0 ahead.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team totally outplayed their opponents in the first
half, had a total shots of 12 to Tajikistan's one.
</P>
<P>
Early in the second half, the Chinese team continued their
dominance, having three shots at the goal in just 3 minutes.
</P>
<P>
But Tajikistan fought back with their counter-attacks and
levelled the score 1-1 through Zabinov at the 53rd minute.
</P>
<P>
Inspired by the goal, the Tajikistan team played more
aggressively in the following 15 minutes. But their efforts were
turned down by a strong Chinese defence line.
</P>
<P>
Li Jinyu, a second-half substitute, put China 2-1 ahead when he
headed home a cross at the 60th minute.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team had a handful scoring chances thereafter but
failed to convert any of them. They surged to 3-1 ahead thanks to
an own goal by Muminov at the 71st minute.
</P>
<P>
It was China's first win in the second round group
competitions. The group also includes Iran and Oman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
