<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippines Airlines, Cathay Still Engaged in Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong-based Cathay
Pacific Airways is still in the thick of negotiations for a stake
in Philippine Airlines (PAL), a senior Philippine official said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Edgardo Espiritu, Secretary of Finance, said the major
remaining concern is the constitutional limitation over Cathay's
participation in the policy and decision making in PAL.
</P>
<P>
In a radio interview, Espiritu said the government will revive
its bridge financing program for PAL only if it can get foreign
airlines and companies to invest in it.
</P>
<P>
PAL earlier submitted its program to rehabilitate the airline
to the government.
</P>
<P>
Espiritu said that while Cathay remains concerned about the
constitutional limitation, it has shown willingness to accept the
conditions of a management-proposed "industrial peace" pact.
</P>
<P>
The conditions, he said, include retaining most of PAL's
employees, with a package of benefits for employees and officers
who are willing to retire now. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
