<HEADLINE> Japan Provides Grant in Aid to Pakistani NGOs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Japan has extended 7.5
million rupees (137,967 U.S. dollars) as grant-in-aid to four
non-governmental organizations (NGOs) to assist them in the
implementation of their projects.
</P>
<P>
The four NGOs are now involved in the work related to the
fields of women-in-development (WID) and agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the participants after the signing ceremony held
here Tuesday at the Japanese Embassy, Japanese Ambassador Minoru
Kubota said the Japanese government and the people have cordial
relations with their counterparts in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
He said that Japan invested in various projects in Pakistan
including power projects, agriculture, health and other sectors in
the past.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese government is endeavoring to enhance technical
skills of the Pakistani people by offering them technical
assistance and orientation facilities in various fields, he added.
</P>
<P>
He said that investment in infrastructure and the private
sector would provide impetus to further improve the existing
relations between Pakistan and Japan. 
</P>
