<BODY>
<HEADLINE> DPR Korea Has Potential to Become Diving Power, Says Chinese Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea has everything ready to become a diving power,
a Chinese coach said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Zhou Jihong said she was surprised at
difficulty of their dives when she gave lectures in DPR Korea in
July this year.
</P>
<P>
"China's future arch rival in diving is neither Japan nor
South Korea. It's DPR Korea," said the diver-turned-coach.
</P>
<P>
DPR Korean Ri Ok-rim finished fourth in the women's
three-meter springboard diving, after Chinese Guo Jingjing and
Yang Lan, and Kazakhstan's Irina Vyguzova.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said DPR Korea had a strong gymnastic background and
full support from the government, which both were prerequisites
for being a diving powerhouse.
</P>
<P>
"DPR Korea will make itself as a diving power in future,"
Zhou said, "just as we did 20 years ago."
</P>
<P>
Zhou won China's first-ever Olympic diving gold medal in the
1984 Games in Los Angeles, United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
