<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- China's Press and Publications
Administration has given approval for the country's eight leading
high-tech business firms to start three electronic publishing
houses for electronic publications.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Hope Computer Corp., the country's largest software
developer and manufacturer, is among the eight companies given the
go-ahead.
</P>
<P>
"Allowing business firms to run their own electronic publishing
houses will be a positive measure for protecting the interests of
the national software developers and cracking down on the piracy
of intellectual property," said Prof. Zhou Mingtao, president of
Beijing Hope Computer Corp.
</P>
