<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia Firm Issues New Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Minzu Group in north China's
Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, a company listed on the Shenzhen
Stock Exchange, announced today that it will issue new shares
to fund further development abroad.
</P>
<P>
The group plans to issued the new shares to raise 86.29 million
yuan to fund construction of a Moscow department store covering
7,660 square meters. The project resulted from a 1996 meeting
between the Chinese and Russian premiers.
</P>
<P>
Minzu also plans to join Mongolian enterprises in gold mining
projects.
</P>
<P>
The group, based the Mongolia Autonomous regional capital of
Hohhot, is one of the largest commercial and trade firms operating
in areas inhabited by ethnic groups. Minzu had a 1997 turnover of
257 million yuan, with projections calling for the annual volume
to hit 1.5 billion yuan by the year 2000.  
</P>
