<HEADLINE> 4 Lebanese Children Killed by Leaking Fumes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Poisonous fumes from a leaking
gas boiler killed four Lebanese children as they were taking a
shower at their home, the Daily Star reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of Zeinab Kamal Allam, 13, and her siblings Sarah,
8, Zahra, 6, and Ali, 5, were found Sunday by their mother, who
was downstairs at the time in the family's ground-floor shop in
eastern Beirut.
</P>
<P>
Her suspicions were aroused when the door had been locked for
some time and no voices could be heard coming from the bathroom.
</P>
<P>
By the time the door was broken down, the children were
already unconscious, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the four children were sent to a downtown
hospital, where they were pronounced dead.
</P>
<P>
A public prosecutor has ordered an investigation into the
children's death, a police source said.
</P>
<P>
Forensic tests showed the victims had all inhaled lethal
quantities of butane gas. 
</P>
