<HEADLINE> One Million Beijingers Use Cellular Phones </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Posts and
Telecommunications Administration announced today that the Chinese
capital has over one million cellular phone subscribers, with
eight units for every 100 people.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's first cellular phone subscriber registered in April
1988, and the total number of subscribers stood at 828 by the end
of the year. The number of local mobile phone subscribers has
grown by an average 1,000 people per day over the past decade. The
city has witnessed some 400,000 new subscribers this year alone.
</P>
<P>
The city's mobile phone network features functions for a
monologue net, GSM, DCS, and CDMA. Mobile phone users enjoy access
to call transfers, message boxes, Chinese information and fax
services, as well as the ability to browse on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's mobile phone switchboard offers 1.36 million
lines, and the city has opened 700 local service centers.
</P>
<P>
Mobile phone services link 91 percent of the nation's cities
with more than 30 countries and regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
