<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Development Bank Urges Moodys to Exhibit Objectivity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for the State
Development Bank (SDB) today urged Moodys to exhibit greater
objectivity in order to determine the bank's correct credit rating.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said Moodys' recent decision to lower the bank's
long-term credit rating from A3 to Baa1 was deeply regrettable.
</P>
<P>
He said that the SDB, China's largest government
policy-oriented bank, has played a major role in raising funds for
accelerating infrastructure construction. He also pointed out the
comprehensive government support in terms of capital, liquidity
and various other areas have ensured the bank's healthy financial
condition.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance recently reaffirmed its full
support for the SDB, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"Moodys acted irrationally in lowering the SDB's rating to
a level which fails to tally with the bank's actual situation," said
the spokesman. "We sincerely hope Moodys wills make an effort to
fully understand actual conditions in China and the status of the
SDB in order to issue an objective correct rating." 
</P>
</TEXT>
