<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Industrial Output Continues to Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The growth rate of China's
industrial output continued to rise in November due to the
positive impact of the policy to stimulate domestic demand.
</P>
<P>
Recent figures from the State Statistics Bureau show a
November industrial value-added of 185 billion yuan, up 11 percent
on the same month last year and 0.4 percentage points higher than
in October.
</P>
<P>
The total value-added for the first 11 months of the year hit
1,802.7 billion yuan, up 8.5 percent on the previous year's period.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises and shareholding ventures under
government control recorded a 7.2-percent growth in value-added in
November from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Output levels for various household electric appliances and
telemunications equipment grew rapidly during the month. For
example, output for color TV sets grew by 45.6 percent,
refrigerators by 85.9 percent and mobile telecom equipment by 83.3
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
