<HEADLINE> Ranariddh Welcomes U.N. Resuming Cambodia's Seat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's acting head of
state Prince Norodom Ranariddh Tuesday gave a warm welcome to the
United Nations' decision to resume Cambodia's seat.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that now that Cambodia has a legal new
coalition government and a National Assembly which were formed in
accordance with the Constitution and the results of the election,
it was very normal to resume Cambodia's U.N. seat.
</P>
<P>
"Cambodia needs the U.N. seat because it will help a lot to our
country' economic construction and social development. We hope the
U.N. and the international community will resume their aid to
Cambodia," said the prince, who is also President of the National
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
"It will also greatly help Cambodia to fully return to the
international community, and to strengthen the cooperation and
relationship between the two parties," Ranariddh stressed.
</P>
<P>
The 53rd General Assembly session on Monday adopted by
consensus a Credential Committee recommendation for Cambodia to
reclaim its U.N. seat which had been left vacant since July last
year.
</P>
<P>
Ouch Borith, previously Cambodia's deputy permanent
representative to the United Nations, was named as the new
ambassador. 
