<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, December 8 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Consumers borrowing in this country recorded the
fastest increase in October since July 1996, the Federal Reserve
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Credit outstanding grew at a 9 percent annual rate to a
seasonally adjusted 1.29 trillion U.S. dollars, according to the
U.S. central bank, which is up from rates of 4.9 percent in
September and 3.9 percent in August. (US-Consumer-Borrowing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt said Monday that it has formulated a strategy
till the year 2010 to promote economic growth while bringing down
the unemployment rate.
</P>
<P>
Under the strategy, Egypt is expected to raise its the annual
economic growth rate to 7 percent while bringing the unemployment
rate to less than 3 percent, Minister of State for Planning Zafer
el-Beshri told a forum here organized by the World Bank.
(Egypt-Strategy-Economy)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Union (EU) unemployment rate remained
at 9.8 percent in October, the same as in September, Eurostat
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The EU unemployment rate dropped to below 10 percent for the
first time in six years in September when it fell to 9.8 percent.
(EU-Jobless Rate)
</P>
