NEW DELHI -- India's annual rate of inflation fell to 8.13
percent for the week ended November 21, a sharp fall for the
second successive week.
</P>
<P>
As the growth rate in the prices of food articles continued to
ease, the inflation rate, based on wholesale price index, fell by
0.41 percent in the week following a decline of 0.31 percent to
8.54 percent in the previous week, the Times of India reported
Monday. (India-Inflation)
</P>
