<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia Seizes Record Cocaine in Single Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Australia seized a record haul
of 225 kg of cocaine off its east coast Monday, Australian Justice
and Customs Minister Amanda Vanstone announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine seized from a yacht off Coffs Harbour on Monday
afternoon, about 600 km northeast of Sydney.
</P>
<P>
An intelligence operation over several months by Australian
Customs Service and Australian Federal Police paid off as officers
impounded the yacht and cocaine with an estimated street value of
30 million U.S. dollars, the minister said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The previous record cocaine haul was in 1994 when 174 kg were
found in the northern Sydney suburb of Artarmon.
</P>
<P>
A federal police spokesman said two Australian men, a Spanish
woman, and the British skipper were arrested in the operation, and
more were expected.
</P>
<P>
The drugs seized had been stored in a dinghy attached to the
vessel, the spokesman said, adding the bust followed a six-month
undercover operation.
</P>
<P>
He said it was believed the yacht, Ketch Maeva, had started its
journey from South America.
</P>
<P>
The seizure comes two months after federal police, customs and
the Australian navy smashed an international drug ring and
recorded Australia's largest ever drug haul.
</P>
<P>
On October 14, during a pre-dawn raid on a beach on the New
South Wales mid-north coast, south of Port Macquarie, 400 kg of
high-grade heroin was seized. 
</P>
</TEXT>
