<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 8 (Xinhua) -- China's world champion Wu
Yanyan, who suffered a humiliating loss to Japanese Yasuko Tajima
in the women's 400m individual medley final on Monday, is set to
win the 200m medley in the Asian Games, his coach said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Wu Jicai said Wu took it too easy at the first
100 meters of yesterday's race and failed to catch up in the
later stages.
</P>
