<HEADLINE> Beijing Increases Landscaped Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, the Chinese capital,
has increased its landscaped areas by 149 million sq.m. over the
past two decades since the introduction of reform and opening.
</P>
<P>
Statistics through the end of 1997 indicate a 34.2 percent
coverage for landscaped areas, up 12 percent from that in 1978,
with the per capita coverage rising by 3.8 sq.m. to 7.8 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
The increased coverage has largely been attributed to extensive
landscaping projects in urban, suburban and mountainous areas.
</P>
<P>
Beijingers enjoy greenery throughout the year, and breathe much
cleaner air due to large-scale suburban afforestation and the
Sanbei (north, northwest and northeast China) Shelterbelt
Project.  
