<P>
SHANGHAI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- China Pacific Insurance
Co. (CPIC), the nation's second largest insurer, has provided 150
million yuan in insurance coverage for members of the Chinese
delegation participating in the 13th Asian Games which opened in
Bangkok on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The personal injury policies cover some 1,000 members of the
delegation, including athletes, as well as administrative,
logistics and technical personnel.
</P>
<P>
Each athlete is covered with a 100,000 yuan policy, with the
remaining members of the delegation provided coverage of 50,000
yuan. Additional 100,000 yuan policies cover athletes during
competitive events.
</P>
<P>
The policy is automatically extended one year for all medalists.
</P>
<P>
A representative from the CPIC Beijing Branch is attending the
games in Bangkok to handle any insurance related problems.
</P>
<P>
The CPIC wrote life insurance policies for Chineses delegation
attending the 25th Olympic Games held in Barcelona in 1996, and
the 12th Asian Games in Hiroshima in 1994.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
