<HEADLINE> French Troops Set up Air Link to Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, December 7 (Xinhua) -- French troops set up an air link
on Monday to transport more NATO soldiers into Macedonia, the
Albanian news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The first 120 French members of a NATO rapid reaction force
arrived in Skopje's Petrovec Airport on four planes from southern
France's Istres air base.
</P>
<P>
They will be deployed at Kumanove base, north Skopje.
</P>
<P>
An additional eight aircraft and three helicopters were also
expected to arrive in Skopje later.
</P>
<P>
British, Italian and Dutch troops, as well as more French
soldiers, are set to arrive in Macedonia within 10 days by way of
the French air link.
</P>
<P>
NATO and Macedonia reached an agreement on November 13 to
station a 1,700 rapid reaction force in the country.
</P>
<P>
The multinational force will guarantee the safety of 2,000
monitors in Kosovo being deployed by the Organization for Security
and Cooperation in Europe (OSCE). 
</P>
</TEXT>
