<HEADLINE> Shanghai Students Lead in Computer Literacy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's largest
industrial and financial center, has placed priority on providing
a computer education for young students.
</P>
<P>
The eastern China municipality has used various approaches to
expand the computer literacy of middle and high school students.
</P>
<P>
Local primary, middle and high schools are currently equipped
with over 20,000 computers, with three institutions on the list of
the China's 18 "national pilot computer instruction schools".
</P>
<P>
Computer education has been gradually expanded to kindergartens
and educational institutions for both physically and mentally
impaired children.
</P>
<P>
Some 117,000 middle school and over 198,000 high school
students in the city have earned computer qualification
certificates.
</P>
<P>
Local students have won a number of national and international
prizes in computer competitions held throughout the 1990s.
</P>
