<HEADLINE> Chinese Farmer Establishes Peony Gene Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, December 8 (Xinhua) -- Chen Dezhong, a farmer in
Lanzhou, capital of northwest China's Gansu Province, has
succeeded in establishing a 12-ha peony cultivation zone, the
largest peony gene base in the region.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 varieties of peonies have been developed in the
Heping Township base, with most of them featuring petals with
beautiful purple spots.
</P>
<P>
Chen has planted and cultivated 150 varieties from central
China, as well as 100 wild varieties from the Tibet Autonomous
Region and Yunnan and Sichuan provinces in southwest China, as
well as Japan.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 individual plants are sold annually in China,
Japan, the United States and Europe.  
</P>
</TEXT>
