<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Plans New Migrant Policies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 8 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Municipal Committee
(BMC) of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference
has suggested new economic measures in managing the city's many
and ever increasing migrants from other Chinese regions.
</P>
<P>
The measures were put forth in a newly finished report of the
Social and Law Committee (SLC) of the BMC's Standing Committee
after a four-month investigation, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
During the investigation, SLC members listened to the reports
from the Beijing Migrants Managerial Office (BMMO) and municipal
governmental departments involved in all aspects of a migrant's
life, carried out on-the-spot investigations in several migrant
neighborhoods, and held symposiums on the topic.
</P>
<P>
The SLC suggested three economic measures to facilitate
Beijing's management of its migrants.
</P>
<P>
The first is to adopt a higher managerial fee on those
migrants coming to the city to run a business or work for one.
</P>
<P>
"Since Beijing doesn't collect an extra Urban Facility Charge
of 50 yuan (6 US dollars) per month on each migrant like Shanghai,
Beijing's managerial fee is actually too low," said BMMO official
Ding Lin.
</P>
<P>
This includes increasing the original 15 yuan (1.8 US dollars)
professional categories fee waivers, and charging more for people
living in Beijing's eight downtown districts with their families.
</P>
<P>
The report also recommends the municipal government impose
taxes on property, operation, the use of the land of cities and
towns, defending city construction, as well as education fee for
people leasing houses.
</P>
<P>
Finally, a settlement fee, the report suggests, should be
imposed on State-owned businesses employing migrants.
</P>
<P>
"Through this, we can somehow level the costs of employing
migrants and of local people, which is always much higher than the
former," Zhang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981208.0348 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-08 </DATE_TIME>
