<HEADLINE> Carbone Brace Chops Down Forest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Benito Carbone broke his goal
drought in 18 matches on Monday to lift Sheffield Wednesday to a
3-2 victory over Nottingham Forest in a English Premier League
match.
</P>
<P>
The little Italian struck twice in four second-half minutes as
Wednesday won their second successive match at Hillsborough
following last month's 3-1 defeat of Manchester United.
</P>
<P>
Niclas Alexandersson, who grabbed a brace himself against
United 16 days ago, scored the opening goal in the 22nd minute of
the match and his teammate Benito Carbone netted twice in the
second half.
</P>
<P>
Forest battled gamely in the final 15 minutes to end a run of
12 league games without a win stretching back to August. But they
had only the consolation of goals by Thierry Bonalair and Pierre
Van Hooijdonk to show for a spirited night's work.
</P>
<P>
They remain just one point clear of bottom club Southampton.
</P>
</TEXT>
