<HEADLINE> IMF Approves Emergency Assistance to Honduras </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary
Fund (IMF) Monday approved Honduras' request for emergency
financial assistance against natural disasters.
</P>
<P>
The assistance, equivalent to some 66 million U.S. dollars,
will support the government's economic recovery program and
associated relief and rehabilitation efforts in the aftermath of
Hurricane Mitch.
</P>
<P>
Honduras joined the IMF in December 1945. Its quota is some
133 million dollars and its outstanding use of IMF financing
currently totals about 45 million dollars. 
</P>
