<HEADLINE> Injured Seizinger May Retire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 7 (Xinhua) -- Injured double Olympic ski
champion Katja Seizinger said on Monday she would miss the season
and may even have to retire, local television quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
During a training crash in Italy in June, she damaged
ligaments in both her knees and fractured the top of her left
shin.
</P>
<P>
Seizinger won the downhill and combined event at the Nagano
Games in February and also took the overall World Cup title.
</P>
<P>
As one of the most successful women in Alpine skiing,
Seizinger has secured 36 world Cup titles. She became overall
champion for the first time in 1996.
</P>
<P>
But now, she said she was facing a bleak racing future.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
