<HEADLINE> Batty Transfer Fee Agreed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 7 (Xinhua) -- The long running saga of David
Batty's proposed return to Leeds looks to be over with news that
the club have agreed a 4.4 million pounds fee with Newcastle.
</P>
<P>
A spokesperson for Batty's agent said on Monday: "The move is
subject to a medical and finalising personal terms, which will
probably be tomorrow morning.
</P>
<P>
"We have no reservations other than we hope the medical goes
according to plan and we don't foresee any problem with personal
terms."
</P>
<P>
Batty started as a trainee at Leeds in 1987 and helped them to
the League title in 1992, before leaving Elland Road in a 2.75
million move five years ago.
</P>
<P>
He had a transfer request accepted by Newcastle 10 days ago
but since then the two clubs have been arguing over a fee.
</P>
<P>
The Yorkshiremen had an original bid of 4 million rejected,
with the Magpies believed to be wanting closer to 6 million.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old has agreed to waive 800,000 in signing-on
bonuses, negotiated when he signed a new five-year contract at
Newcastle in the close season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
