<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2140GMT, December 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran announced Monday that nearly 1,500 kilograms of
narcotics were seized from Afghan traffickers in the northeastern
Khorasan province in the past two days.
</P>
<P>
The official Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) quoted a
report from the provincial security forces as saying that the
drugs included 106 kilograms of heroin and 1386 kilograms of
opium. (BC-Iran-Drug Haul)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- The 19th session of the summit of the Gulf
Cooperation Council (GCC) opened here Monday evening to explore
ways to cement regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the six member states of the GCC will review the
recent developments in the region and seek unified stands in
various fields at the three-day summit. (BC-GCC-Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Dozens of Palestinians were injured in West Bank
Monday when Israeli soldiers clamped down on their demonstrations
for the release of Palestinian prisoners.
</P>
<P>
At least 20 Palestinians were lightly hurt as they clashed
with Israeli soldiers who guarded a Jewish holy site near
Bethlehem. The demonstrators threw stones at the soldiers, who
responded with rubber-coated bullets and tear gas.
(BC-Palestine-Demonstrations)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- A Sudanese opposition leader said here Monday that the
National Democratic Alliance (NDA) of Sudan will discuss possible
actions against the government in a meeting in Cairo.
</P>
<P>
After a meeting with Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa,
former Sudanese Prime Minister al-Sadeq al-Mahdi said the NDA
meeting will come in light of the need for an understanding at the
highest level of the group. (BC-Egypt-Sudan-Opposition Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan stressed Monday
the importance of the partnership between the U.N. and the Gulf
cooperation Council (GCC).
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony of the GCC summit here, Annan
said that "the partnership between the U.N. and GCC is of the
utmost importance -- especially in the field of peacemaking and
preventive diplomacy."
</P>
<P>
Annan, the first U.N. chief to attend the GCC summit, said
Regional organizations such as the GCC are U.N.'s most important
partners and allies. "They serve to both complement and support
the U.N.'s work," he said. (BC-GCC-Annan-Speech)
</P>
<P>
